Luigi's has the best pizza by the slice in town...period! The crust is excellent as well as the sauce. They serve great desserts and good pasta/panini. It is best to visit during lunch if you want a slice, otherwise order a whole pie so it is fresh. Business slows down from 2-5 so they don't make a lot of fresh slices. That being said, even an older slice of Luigi's pizza still annihilates Spinelli's or Butchertown Pizza. Please give this place a try. If I could afford it, I would buy everyone a Luigi's pizza!!! BTW Luigi, I would love it if you guys could deliver...or stay open later...or both. Thanks for the pizza!!

Working in the street directly in front of the establishment, we were constantly bombarded with smells and promises that the food just couldn't keep. I gave them 3 chances to impress me. I REALLY wanted to like this place.  First chance, I tried the meatball sandwich. It was like eating a pizza crust foodball with 4 meatballs and a little sauce inside. The meatballs had a decent enough flavor, NOT enough filling at all. I came back from my lunch break feeling like I had just been working overtime by eating that thing.  Next visit we tried the pizza by the slice. It's hard to screw up pizza, but they perfected their craft at it. The pizzas are already premade, sitting there for who knows how long...drying out. You choose which slice(slices if you're wealthy) you want, they throw it back into the oven to reheat, further dehydrating your pizza jerky. You pay the exorbitant price for it and spend the rest of your lunch wondering if you should attempt to reconstitute it with fresh sauce, or give it a proper burial.  Lastly, I had a salad which was actually decent and we both had the ravioli. The meat was devoid of flavor. The marinara was just a step above mediocre. Cannot reccomend.

Can you really call yourself an Italian restaurant if you run out of or don’t serve something basic to the type of food you serve? In my opinion no. I did have a piece of pizza after being shocked first and it was fine. Super thin basic pizza taste nothing special i can’t get from any other actual Italian restaurant at a better price.

So I’m not entirely sure how this place recurved a 4.2 star, but let’s roll with it. So we have eaten at this place the last two days. I’m not sure who’s idea it is to cook a pizza, leave it out (uncovered) and warms slices back up to serve to people. The copious amounts of flies are a deal breaker. It’s almost like all the local flies invited all the other flies to come to Luigi’s to eat all the flavor off the pizzas that are left out waiting to be reheated. The pizza is dry as a bone but that’s what happens with left out pizza. Two slices and a soda pop costs twelve bucks and the subway across the street will give you a pizza sub that tastes better than Luigi’s pizza and you’ll pay a lot less. The waiting line is a cluster F. And the soda dispenser is right at the front of the dysfunctional line. So if you want a drink, you’ll have to wait to be trapped and refill your beverage.

The strombolis are a total joke, mostly (stale) bread, barely any mozzarella or condiments accompanied with 1 maybe 2 slices of pepperoni = NO TASTE❗ ......and the sauce, the sauce is pathetic, bland/tastless❗Sorry to say, but this place needs new management. I will 100%  never go back, heed my warning ppl. Save your money & go to subway across the street. It's 100 x  better than this so-called Italian pizzeria. We travel to Louisville every year for the SkillsUSA conference/contest for a week in June and we bring approx. 15 students with us every year.  While in Louisville we always take in the sites and walk down museum roll.  This year we found Luigi's Pizzeria and Pasta and when you have high school age people with you pizza is always a popular choice of food.  Now, I have eaten a lot of pizza over the years with many students but, this was a culinary delight.  We all enjoyed our meals and vowed we would return again and again in the future.  If you are looking for a GREAT pizza place to eat at then we highly suggest Luigi's, you will not be disappointed.
